content: I paid for a sorry not working message, try again later. 2-9-21: after uninstalling, and reinstalling a couple times. It is up and running. Thank you.
I also paid for a "sorry something went wrong" message.
Not all videos work, some do but not all.
Bookmarks erase after closing app. FIX IT
Getting better but still way off par. Why bother giving the option to make bookmarks if they reset when I open the app back up?
The search doesn't work well. Much bigger issue is that the text gets cut off at the end of paragraphs making it impossible to interpret. You have to have the book so this app is useless.
Great app. All the baseball and softball rules in my pocket at all times. Love the search feature for quick and easy lookup.

Search options are difficult - trying to find specific rules about Manager's kids for Tryouts has been fruitless. As soon as you open a page, your search results all disappear. I've never had to spend this much time looking through our paperback books to find necessary answers to our questions.

Why isn't this available like all of my other apps from Google? I can have this app on my tablet and on my computer, since they are both mine and registered in my name. This totally sucks and a waste of my money

As of 2/2020, bookmarks are erased as soon as the app is closed. If you leave the app open and switch to another app, it will occasionally reset the view to the start screen, making you lose your place in the rulebook. The failure of the bookmark tool makes this very annoying. The search function works at a basic level, but it isn't a smart search, because minor misspellings return no results and related words aren't used in the search. Search history is saved, though. It needs basic fixes.
None to be able to search. However bookmarks don't seem to save, and need to be able to make text larger.
Type is small and unable to zoom in. Also, rules pages are clearly cut off, not giving full detail or description of content for each section.
Where's the videos? No videos on Android?

Print/font very small. Not able to explode/expand for easier reading. Does not turn to allow for viewing as horizontal (wide vs tall). Afraid that in bright light like very sunny day text will be unreadable. No back button that allows for return to exact spot after checking suggested links. App returns to the beginning and you must search to return to prior spot.

It works in my Samsung Galaxy S10, but the search function is lacking. For example, searching "tryout" gives you multiple responses and none of them are what I was looking for. As a DA looking for quick answers at my desk, this will not suffice.
I have a galaxy S10 and not all the rules are complete in the App. Player eligibility for example just cuts off at "player age is defined as"
Still not working on my older android. Not an acceptable substitution for a DA. Would give 0 stars if allowed.
All rule books open fine now.
replyContent:
Apologies for the inconvenience you've had with the Rulebook App. At the time of your review, we experienced an 
unexpected bug that caused for some Rulebooks to not load properly. The bug has been fixed and the app is working properly now. If you restart the app and it still crashes, we recommend deleting the app and then re-downloading the app.

content: Rule books will not open on Galaxy Note 9 with Android 9. Table of Contents flashes up for a second, then white screen.
replyContent: Apologies for the inconvenience you've had with the Rulebook App. We experienced an unexpected bug that caused for some Rulebooks to not load properly. The bug has been fixed and the app is working properly. If you restart the app and it still crashes, we recommend deleting the app and re-downloading. New bug fixes and updates are coming soon!

content: I would give it five stars but you have no way to highlight which the past app allowed for you to do that.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback on the Rulebook app. Highlighting, creating notes, and bookmarking specific content or rule clauses are some features we are considering for development in 2020.
